    "This was not ideal when considering the balance of training data for trial and movement type.",
    "To address this, we instituted a \"lock mode\" where the non-active cursor's motion was fixed so that the participant was able to focus on the cursor which was cued to move during unimanual trials.",
    "We used cross-validated estimates of Euclidean distance for the quantification of neural tuning strength and other statistics requiring Euclidean distance, such as Pearson's correlation between groups of linear model tuning coefficients.",
    "These methods are discussed in greater detail in our prior report 27 (Willett*, Deo*, et al.",
    "2020; see code repository https:// github."
